      <h3>
        <a name="683"></a>SFA Charter School Extended Closure
      </h3>
      <p>
        Update March 31, 2020 - UPDATE REGARDING COVID-19 (coronavirus)<br><br>
        SFA Charter School Families,<br>
        Today, Texas Governor Greg Abbott extended school closures until May 4, 2020 due to the threat from COVID-19 (coronavirus). SFA Charter School must remain closed for in-person instruction as required.<br>
        SFA Charter School has no confirmed cases, but Nacogdoches County has two confirmed cases, with 3,266 confirmed in Texas. As we continue to receive school updates regarding the COVID-19 (coronavirus) conditions, you may expect communication through email, social media, and websites.<br>
        Through Seesaw, our individualized online instructional platform, teachers continue to provide rich learning opportunities for our SFA Charter School students while out of school. Teachers delight in the time spent engaging with students each day.<br>
        If we work together, fewer friends and family will be affected by coronavirus. Hospitals will not be overloaded and lives will be saved. Learn more at <a href="http://www.texas.gov/covid19">www.texas.gov/covid19</a> 
      </p>
      <p>
         <a target="_blank" href="http://www.texas.gov/covid19"><img alt="COVID-19 graphic" src="/charter_school/images/COVIDpic-tn.png"></a>
      </p>
      <h3>
        <a name="96"></a>Charter Program Description
      </h3>
      <p>
        The SFA Charter Campus is based on the twin goals of improving public education and enhancing the preparation of future educators and school psychologists. The school serves as a Field Based Center for the College of Education and provides "hands-on" and observational experiences with children for university students in Elementary Education, Kinesiology, Music, School Psychology, and other university instructional programs.
      </p>
      <p>
        The SFA Charter School mission is to create a responsive social learning community which inspires autonomy, integrity, and deep critical thinking.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a target="_blank" href="/charter_school/SFA_Charter_School_Flowchart_(05.22.2019).pdf">SFACS Organization Chart </a> 
      </p>
